==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*nimman'', probably from Indo-European ''*nem-'' ‘take’.

Germanic cognates include Old High German ''[[neman]]'' (German ''[[nehmen]]''), Old Saxon ''[[niman]]'' (Dutch ''[[nemen]]''), Old Norse ''[[nema]]'' (Danish ''[[nemme]]''), Gothic [[𐌽𐌹𐌼𐌰𐌽]].  The IE root was also the source of Old Irish ''[[nem]]'' ‘present’, Latvian ''[[nams]]'', Greek ''[[νέμειν]]''.

